 392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her best form\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 369}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She failed to make the final of the 100m last week after clocking a disappointing time of 11.1sec in her semi-final.\", \"from\": 394, \"to\": 510, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 100m\", \"from\": 426, \"to\": 434}, {\"ngram\": \"a disappointing time\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 480}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And she cut an unhappy figure when she was well short of American Gabby Thomas in Monday night's semi-finals of the 200m.\", \"from\": 512, \"to\": 633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 569, \"end\": 577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999998978238249, \"rank\": 8.385012548010442e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 578, \"end\": 590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9999999994633981, \"rank\": 5.365356455671634e-10, \"text\": \"Gabby Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabrielle_Thomas\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an unhappy figure\", \"from\": 524, \"to\": 541}, {\"ngram\": \"Monday night's semi\", \"from\": 594, \"to\": 613}, {\"ngram\": \"finals\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 620}, {\"ngram\": \"the 200m.\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 633}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas is the overwhelming favourite for gold, so it is perhaps wrong to compare like for like, but Asher-Smith, a former world champion for the distance, looks set to miss out on being in medal contention tonight.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 635, \"end\": 641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.5799343583973019, \"rank\": 0.7239245177204999, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the overwhelming favourite\", \"from\": 645, \"to\": 671}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 680}, {\"ngram\": \"Asher-Smith\", \"from\": 735, \"to\": 746}, {\"ngram\": \"a former world champion\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 771}, {\"ngram\": \"the distance\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 788}, {\"ngram\": \"medal contention\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 840}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She had continued to talk positively up until last night, when she opted for near-enough silence after her 200m run of 22.31sec.\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"last night\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 907}, {\"ngram\": \"near-enough silence\", \"from\": 928, \"to\": 947}, {\"ngram\": \"22.31sec\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 978}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All she said was: \\\"It was good, because I did not use much energy.\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 1047, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"much energy\", \"from\": 1035, \"to\": 1046}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am saving what I can for tomorrow.\\\"\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1085, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"tomorrow\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1083}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And yet she has been the benchmark for British sprinting - male or female - for years now.\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1177, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the benchmark\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1121}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1172}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has two Olympic medals and six medals at World Championship level, so a backlog of work to suggest she is a championship performer, able to repeatedly deliver on the biggest stage.\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1362, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two Olympic medals\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1204}, {\"ngram\": \"six medals\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1219}, {\"ngram\": \"World Championship level\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1247}, {\"ngram\": \"a backlog\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1261}, {\"ngram\": \"work\", \"from\": 1265, \"to\": 1269}, {\"ngram\": \"a championship performer\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1312}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest stage\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1361}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Plus, the 200m has habitually been her stronger event.\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1417, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 200m\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1377}, {\"ngram\": \"her stronger event\", \"from\": 1398, \"to\": 1416}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Asher-Smith ended her long-time coaching relationship with John Blackie last year and relocated to the United States in the wake of last year's World Championships, where she trains with the likes of Julien Alfred, the sprinter from St Lucia who sealed the 100m gold.\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1483, \"end\": 1490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blackie_and_Son\", \"score\": 0.9999999999795364, \"rank\": 2.0612353753617736e-11, \"text\": \"Blackie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blackie_and_Son\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blackie_and_Son\"}, {\"begin\": 1522, \"end\": 1535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9989962808790753, \"rank\": 0.0008075319233550261, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1652, \"end\": 1660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"score\": 0.9990097093489515, \"rank\": 0.0009912717446090677, \"text\": \"St Lucia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Asher-Smith\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1430}, {\"ngram\": \"her long-time coaching relationship\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1472}, {\"ngram\": \"the wake\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1547}, {\"ngram\": \"last year's World Championships\", \"from\": 1551, \"to\": 1582}, {\"ngram\": \"the likes\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1615}, {\"ngram\": \"Julien Alfred\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1632}, {\"ngram\": \"the sprinter\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1646}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100m gold\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1685}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The hope is that Alfred's success may yet rub off over the longer distance, although Asher-Smith finds herself in a fight to be even Britain's fastest woman withDaryll Neita.\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1862, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1821, \"end\": 1828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9975299414779822, \"rank\": 0.002475957384205534, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The hope\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1696}, {\"ngram\": \"Alfred's success\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1721}, {\"ngram\": \"the longer distance\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1762}, {\"ngram\": \"Asher-Smith\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1784}, {\"ngram\": \"a fight\", \"from\": 1802, \"to\": 1809}, {\"ngram\": \"Neita\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 1861}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Neita reached the final of the 100m and finished fourth, and was just shy of her personal best in a time of 22.24sec in the 200m semi-finals, an event in which she currently lacks the experience of Asher-Smith.\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 2074, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"